interaction_depth_values = [3, 10]
n_trees_values = [100,300,500]
shrinkage_values = [0.05,1, 0.07]

# Create all possible combinations of hyperparameters
gbm_grid = {
    'max_depth': interaction_depth_values,
    'n_estimators': n_trees_values,
    'learning_rate': shrinkage_values
}

# Convert the dictionary to a DataFrame
#gbm_grid_df = pd.DataFrame(gbm_grid)

# Create a Gradient Boosting classifier
gb_classifier = GradientBoostingClassifier(random_state=1)

# Perform grid search using cross-validated search over the specified parameter grid
grid_search2 = GridSearchCV(estimator=gb_classifier,
                           param_grid=gbm_grid,  # You can add hyperparameters if needed
                           scoring='accuracy',
                           cv=7)  # 5-fold cross-validation

In [ ]:
def plot_importance(model, features, num=len(Data), save=False):
    feature_imp = pd.DataFrame({'Value': model.feature_importances_, 'Feature': features.columns})
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 10))
    sns.set(font_scale=1)
    sns.barplot(x="Value", y="Feature", data=feature_imp.sort_values(by="Value",
                                                                     ascending=False)[0:num])
    plt.title('Features')
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
    if save:
        plt.savefig('importances.png')
